<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-2232] Mail component sends to the wrong address</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-2232</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The camel mail page states that the issues with the Mail Component are related to geronimo.  However there is a fundamental problem when you have more than 1 endpoint defined.  We define multiple endpoints so we can place different To addresses&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        &amp;lt;endpoint id=&quot;oneEmail&quot; uri=&quot;smtp://MAILSERVER?To=${one.email}&amp;amp;From=blah@blah.com&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;endpoint id=&quot;twoEmail&quot; uri=&quot;smtp://MAILSERVER?To=${two.email}&amp;amp;From=blah@blah.com&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;endpoint id=&quot;errorEmail&quot; uri=&quot;smtp://MAILSERVER?To=${error.email}&amp;amp;From=blah@blah.com&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;            &amp;lt;to uri=&quot;bean:errorFormatter?method=formatErrorEmail&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;to ref=&quot;errorEmail&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is not possible to configure the uri in &amp;lt;to /&amp;gt; since it does not support spring properties.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The bug is that MailConfiguration.copy() does not create a new Map for recipients, so when the second endpoint is created it overwrites the first. there are other fields that may be affected e.g. javaMailProperties, additionalJavaMailProperties, javaMailSender&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://camel.apache.org/mail.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://camel.apache.org/mail.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
If you have trouble with sending mails that, for instance, don&apos;t contain any subject, have wrong recipients, or manifest other unforeseen errors, it could be due to having geronimo-javamail_1.4_spec-1.3.jar in your classpath. This was the culprit in a long bug hunt reported in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-869&quot; title=&quot;A subject from message header is not copied to mailMessage &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-869&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-869&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This should be changed as wrong recipients are more likely related to camel bugs, than geronimo issues.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
